## The 3 List Patterns and Their Realtime Integration

### Pattern A — TanStack Query lists (most lists)

```tsx
// The hook fires onEvent → call the existing invalidation helper
useRealtimeSync({
  table: "party_contacts",
  event: "*",
  filter: `party_id=eq.${partyId}`,   // scope to current entity when applicable
  onEvent: () => invalidatePartyContacts(queryClient, partyId),
  enabled: !!partyId,
});
```

### Pattern B — Server-props lists (Parties, DMS Documents)

```tsx
// Server-rendered pages use router.refresh() to trigger a new server fetch
useRealtimeSync({
  table: "parties",
  event: "*",
  onEvent: () => router.refresh(),
});
```

### Pattern C — Hybrid state (Employees)

```tsx
// Call the existing data-fetch callback from the component
useRealtimeSync({
  table: "employees",
  event: "*",
  onEvent: () => fetchEmployees(page, pageSize, search, filters),
});
```

